  "prompt": "What is the legal framework surrounding money laundering?",
  "response": "The legal framework surrounding money laundering typically involves several key components:\n\n1. International Regulations\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention Against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n\n2. National Legislation\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) laws\n- Bank Secrecy Act\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) requirements\n- Reporting obligations for financial institutions\n\n3. Key Legal Provisions\n- Criminalizing money laundering activities\n- Establishing reporting requirements\n- Mandating customer due diligence\n- Implementing transaction monitoring systems\n\n4. Compliance Requirements\n- Financial institutions must report suspicious transactions\n- Maintain detailed transaction records\n- Conduct customer risk assessments\n- Implement internal control mechanisms\n\n5. Enforcement Mechanisms\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Asset seizure\n- Substantial financial penalties\n- Potential imprisonment for offenders\n\n6. Regulatory Oversight\n- Government financial intelligence units\n- Central bank supervision\n- Regular compliance audits\n- Mandatory training programs\n\nThese frameworks aim to prevent, detect, and prosecute money laundering activities across different jurisdictions.",
